data.title: Long before she became a music superstar, Beyoncé Knowles-Carter spent the first 21 years of her life growing up in Houston's Third Ward...
data.meta_description:
844 likes, 20 comments - houstonchron on July 27, 2022: "Long before she became a music superstar, Beyoncé Knowles-Carter spent the first 21 years of her life growing up in Houston's Third Ward and later Missouri City.⁠
⁠
Although she’s since moved elsewhere, in Houston, @beyonce 's love for H-Town still runs deep, according to those who know her best.⁠
She shouts the city's name in songs, films music videos here, and even takes in the culture on visits, making stops at local faves like the @menilcollection, @katfishandgrits and BBs Cafe.⁠
⁠
More importantly, she pours millions into helping the homeless and disenfranchised nationwide and in the city she still calls home.⁠
⁠
As we all prepare for the release of #renaissance, including @mstinalawson, click the link in the bio of the music icon’s long history of giving back to Houston.⁠
#htx #beyonce".
